# Góc Nhìn Máy Quay Phim -- Camera View
msgid "Camera View"
msgstr "Góc Nhìn Máy Quay Phim"

msgid "Demonstration of camera view."
msgstr "Demonstration of camera view."

msgid "The Camera view shows the current scene as seen from the currently active camera's view point."
msgstr "The Camera view shows the current scene as seen from the currently active camera's view point."

msgid "The Camera view can be used to virtually compose shots and preview how the scene will look when rendered. The rendered image will contain everything within the dashed line."
msgstr "The Camera view can be used to virtually compose shots and preview how the scene will look when rendered. The rendered image will contain everything within the dashed line."

msgid ":doc:`Camera Settings </render/cameras>` for details how camera settings are used for display & rendering."
msgstr ":doc:`Sắp Đặt Của Máy Quay Phim -- Camera Settings </render/cameras>` for details how camera settings are used for display & rendering."

msgid "The active camera can be selected while in camera view using the camera frame *(assuming the object isn't hidden).*"
msgstr "The active camera can be selected while in camera view using the camera frame *(assuming the object isn't hidden).*"

msgid "Viewing the Active Camera"
msgstr "Viewing the Active Camera"

# Tham Chiếu -- Reference
msgid "Reference"
msgstr "Tham Chiếu"

msgid "Mode"
msgstr "Chế Độ"

msgid "All modes"
msgstr "Tổng Thể"

msgid "Menu"
msgstr "Trình Đơn"

# :menuselection:`View --> Cameras --> Active Camera`
msgid ":menuselection:`View --> Cameras --> Active Camera`"
msgstr ":menuselection:`Góc Nhìn (View) --> Máy Quay Phim (Camera) --> Máy Quay Phim Đang Hoạt Động (Active Camera)`"

msgid "Hotkey"
msgstr "Phím Tắt"

msgid ":kbd:`Numpad0`"
msgstr ":kbd:`:kbd:`Số 0 Bàn Số (Numpad0)``"

msgid "This switches the view to the active camera. The triangle above the camera will become shaded when active."
msgstr "This switches the view to the active camera. The triangle above the camera will become shaded when active."

msgid "Setting the Active Camera"
msgstr "Setting the Active Camera"

msgid "Object Mode"
msgstr "Chế Độ Vật Thể"

# :menuselection:`View --> Cameras --> Set Active Camera`
msgid ":menuselection:`View --> Cameras --> Set Active Camera`"
msgstr ":menuselection:`Góc Nhìn (View) --> Máy Quay Phim (Camera) --> Máy Quay Phim Đang Hoạt Động (Active Camera)`"

# :kbd:`:kbd:`Ctrl-Số 0 Bàn Số (Numpad0)``
msgid ":kbd:`Ctrl-Numpad0`"
msgstr ":kbd:`Ctrl-Alt-Numpad0`"

msgid "Active camera (left) displayed with a solid triangle above it."
msgstr "Active camera (left) displayed with a solid triangle above it."

msgid "This is the camera currently used for rendering and when viewing from the camera."
msgstr "This is the camera currently used for rendering and when viewing from the camera."

msgid "This sets the current active object as the active camera & switches to the camera view."
msgstr "This sets the current active object as the active camera & switches to the camera view."

msgid "The active camera can also be set in the *Scene* tab of the *Properties Editor*."
msgstr "The active camera can also be set in the *Cảnh -- Scene* tab of the *Trình Biên Soạn Tính Chất -- Properties Editor*."

msgid "The active camera, as well as the layers, can be specific to a given view, or global (locked) to the whole scene. See :doc:`Local Camera </editors/3dview/properties/sidebar>`."
msgstr "The active camera, as well as the layers, can be specific to a given view, or global (locked) to the whole scene. See :doc:`Máy Quay Phim Cục Bộ -- Local Camera </editors/3dview/properties/sidebar>`."

msgid "Animated Camera Switching"
msgstr "Animated Camera Switching"

msgid "By default a scene contains one camera. However, a scene can contain more than one camera, but only one of them will be used at a time. So you will only need to add a new camera if you are making cuts between them. See :ref:`Animating Cameras <marker-bind-camera>`."
msgstr "By default a scene contains one camera. However, a scene can contain more than one camera, but only one of them will be used at a time. So you will only need to add a new camera if you are making cuts between them. See :ref:`Animating Cameras <marker-bind-camera>`."

# Điều Hướng Máy Quay Phim -- Camera Navigation
msgid "Camera Navigation"
msgstr "Điều Hướng Máy Quay Phim"

msgid "There are several different ways to navigate and position the camera in your scene, some of them are explained below."
msgstr "There are several different ways to navigate and position the camera in your scene, some of them are explained below."

msgid "Zooming in and out is possible in this view, but to change the viewpoint, you have to move or rotate the camera."
msgstr "Zooming in and out is possible in this view, but to change the viewpoint, you have to move or rotate the camera."

msgid "The active \"camera\" might be any kind of object. So these actions can be used, for example, to position and aim a light."
msgstr "The active \"camera\" might be any kind of object. So these actions can be used, for example, to position and aim a light."

# Chuyển Máy Quay Phim Đang Hoạt Động Đến Góc Nhìn -- Move Active Camera to View
msgid "Move Active Camera to View"
msgstr "Chuyển Máy Quay Phim Đang Hoạt Động Đến Góc Nhìn"

msgid ":kbd:`Ctrl-Alt-Numpad0`"
msgstr ":kbd:`:kbd:`Ctrl-Alt-Số 0 Bàn Số (Numpad0)``"

msgid "This matches the active camera to a regular (non camera) view, for a convenient method of placing the camera without having to move the object directly."
msgstr "This matches the active camera to a regular (non camera) view, for a convenient method of placing the camera without having to move the object directly."

# Định Vị Góc Nhìn Máy Quay Phim -- Camera View Positioning
msgid "Camera View Positioning"
msgstr "Định Vị Góc Nhìn Máy Quay Phim"

# By enabling :ref:`Chốt Máy Quay vào Góc Nhìn -- Lock Camera to View <3dview-lock-camera-to-view>` in the View panel of the Sidebar region, while in camera view, you can navigate the 3D View as usual, while remaining in camera view. Controls are exactly the same as when normally moving in 3D.
msgid "By enabling :ref:`Lock Camera to View <3dview-lock-camera-to-view>` in the View panel of the Sidebar region, while in camera view, you can navigate the 3D View as usual, while remaining in camera view. Controls are exactly the same as when normally moving in 3D."
msgstr "By enabling :ref:`Lock Camera to View <3dview-lock-camera-to-view>` in the View panel of the Properties region, while in camera view, you can navigate the 3D View as usual, while remaining in camera view. Controls are exactly the same as when normally moving in 3D."

msgid ":ref:`Fly/Walk Mode <3dview-fly-walk>` for first person navigation that moves the active camera too."
msgstr ":ref:`Fly/Walk Mode <3dview-fly-walk>` for first person navigation that moves the active camera too."

# Lăn, Lia, Lướt, và Giám Sát -- Roll, Pan, Dolly, and Track
msgid "Roll, Pan, Dolly, and Track"
msgstr "Lăn, Lia, Lướt, và Giám Sát"

msgid "To perform these camera moves, the camera must first be *selected* so transform operations apply to it."
msgstr "To perform these camera moves, the camera must first be *cái được chọn -- selected* so transform operations apply to it."

msgid "The following actions also assume that you are in camera view."
msgstr "The following actions also assume that you are in camera view."

msgid "Having done so, you can now manipulate the camera using the same tools that are used to transform any object:"
msgstr "Having done so, you can now manipulate the camera using the same tools that are used to transform any object:"

# Xoáy -- Roll
msgid "Roll"
msgstr "Xoáy"

msgid "Press :kbd:`R` to enter object rotation mode. The default will be to rotate the camera in its local Z axis (the axis orthogonal to the camera view), which is the definition of a camera \"roll\"."
msgstr "Press :kbd:`:kbd:`R`` to enter object rotation mode. The default will be to rotate the camera in its local Z axis (the axis orthogonal to the camera view), which is the definition of a camera \"roll\"."

# Lia hoặc Chúc Đầu Lên/Xuống theo chiều Dựng Đứng -- Vertical Pan or Pitch
msgid "Vertical Pan or Pitch"
msgstr "Lia hoặc Chúc Đầu Lên/Xuống theo chiều Dựng Đứng"

# This is just a rotation along the local X axis. Press :kbd:`:kbd:`R`` to enter object rotation mode, then :kbd:`X` twice (the first press selects the *toàn cầu -- global* axis, pressing the same letter a second time selects the *địa phương -- local* axis -- this works with any axis; see the :doc:`axis locking page </scene_layout/object/editing/transform/control/axis_locking>`).
msgid "This is just a rotation along the local X axis. Press :kbd:`R` to enter object rotation mode, then :kbd:`X` twice (the first press selects the *global* axis, pressing the same letter a second time selects the *local* axis -- this works with any axis; see the :doc:`axis locking page </scene_layout/object/editing/transform/control/axis_locking>`)."
msgstr "This is just a rotation along the local X axis. Press :kbd:`R` to enter object rotation mode, then :kbd:`X` twice (the first press selects the *global* axis, pressing the same letter a second time selects the *local* axis -- this works with any axis; see the :doc:`axis locking page </editors/3dview/object/editing/transform/control/precision/axis_locking>`)."

# Lia hoặc Lúc Lắc theo Chiều Ngang -- Horizontal Pan or Yaw
msgid "Horizontal Pan or Yaw"
msgstr "Lia hoặc Lúc Lắc theo Chiều Ngang"

msgid "This corresponds to a rotation around the camera's local Y axis. Press :kbd:`R`, and then :kbd:`Y` twice."
msgstr "This corresponds to a rotation around the camera's local Y axis. Press :kbd:`:kbd:`R``, and then :kbd:`Y` twice."

# Lướt -- Dolly
msgid "Dolly"
msgstr "Lướt"

msgid "To dolly the camera, press :kbd:`G` then :kbd:`MMB` (or :kbd:`Z` twice)."
msgstr "To dolly the camera, press :kbd:`:kbd:`G`` then :kbd:`:kbd:`NCG (MMB)`` (or :kbd:`Z` twice)."

# Theo Dõi Chuyển Vị Biên -- Sideways Tracking
msgid "Sideways Tracking"
msgstr "Theo Dõi Chuyển Vị Biên"

msgid "Press :kbd:`G` and move the mouse (you can use :kbd:`X` twice or :kbd:`Y` to get pure-horizontal or pure-vertical sideways tracking)."
msgstr "Press :kbd:`:kbd:`G`` and move the mouse (you can use :kbd:`X` twice or :kbd:`Y` to get pure-horizontal or pure-vertical sideways tracking)."

